Phase 2: HuggingFace Model-Loading + Quantization — COMPLETE

Completed: 2026-04-16

## Implemented Methods

### 1. Lazy Loading
- `load_model()` — thread-safe model loading with `threading.Lock`
- `_ensure_model_loaded()` — lazy-load on first `generate()` call
- `_do_load_model()` — internal loading logic (caller holds lock)

### 2. Device Auto-Detection
- `_detect_device()` — CUDA > MPS > CPU priority when `hf_device="auto"`
- Supports explicit device strings: `"cuda"`, `"cuda:0"`, `"cuda:1"`, `"mps"`, `"cpu"`
- Device stored in `self._device` for use during generation

### 3. Quantization
- `_build_quantization_config()` — returns `BitsAndBytesConfig` for:
  - `"4bit"` → NF4 + double quantization + compute dtype
  - `"8bit"` → LLM.int8()
  - `None` → no quantization (full precision)
- `_resolve_dtype()` — auto-selects bfloat16/float16/float32 based on hardware

### 4. Model Loading
- `_do_load_model()` — full implementation:
  - `AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained()` with all config options
  - `AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained()` with caching/token support
  - `hf_cache_dir` for local caching
  - `hf_revision` for version pinning
  - `hf_token` for gated models
  - `hf_trust_remote_code` support
  - `hf_offload_folder` support
  - `device_map="auto"` when appropriate
  - `pad_token = eos_token` fallback
  - Progress logging at each stage
  - Model set to `.eval()` mode after loading

### 5. Memory Management
- `unload_model()` — deletes model/tokenizer, clears GPU cache, runs gc.collect()
- `_try_cpu_fallback()` — automatic OOM fallback: GPU → CPU float32
- `__del__` destructor — cleanup + executor shutdown

### 6. Generation (bonus, part of Phase 2 interface)
- `generate()` — sync generation with lazy-load, OOM handling, tokenization
- `generate_async()` — async wrapper via ThreadPoolExecutor
- `supports_streaming = True`, `supports_async = True`

